memberdef.argsstring: (std::vector< int > problem_id=std::vector< int >(0), std::vector< int > instance_id=std::vector< int >(0), std::vector< int > dimension=std::vector< int >(0))
memberdef.name: IOHprofiler_suite

briefdescription.para: An interface of requesting problems in suite.

detaileddescription.para: To request a specific problem with corresponding problem_id, instance_id and dimension, without concerning the order of testing problems.

briefdescription.para: Return a map of problem name to problem ID, for all the registered problem.
A base class for construct a suite for sets of IOHprofiler_problems.

detaileddescription.para: To specify available problems of a suite, registerProblem must be implemented in derived class. The default lable of problems are string type. Integer type are also optional, but we highly recommond registering problem with string lable and creating a map of string problem_name and integer problem_id.
